Rules-Glitches: Any glitches that can cause the match to be completely unplayable (e.g. by causing a softlock or a game freeze) are banned. A player who triggers such a glitch has to forfeit the current game.
Rules-Notes:
1. Nanami is banned to avoid desyncs and prevent bypassing character switch rules.

2. Chen-Mao players must be aware of the desync issues she can cause and of how to prevent them. If she is selected second on the character select screen, one of her two stages will be randomly selected for the match, which can desynchronize the game during netplay.
	a) The Chen-Mao player is responsible for resetting the game themselves to avoid this (by default, using the F3 key as player 1). As such, any would-be Chen-Mao players must be player 1 and manage resetting the game when necessary. 
		- To be player 1 on Fightcade, you must be the one to challenge your opponent.
		- Any desyncs caused by Chen-Mao will grant the game to their opponent.
		- If a player forgets to reset the game upon a loss and picks Chen-Mao for the next match, the game must be reset before the match starts (FIGHT! appears on screen). Resetting the emulator once the match has started will grant the game to the Chen-Mao player's opponent.
	b) These rules do not apply in case of a Chen-Mao mirror. Avoid desyncs by resetting the emulator after every game. In order to keep the tournament running on time, failure to take these steps may lead to disqualification of both players at an organizer's discretion.

Rules-Notes:
All tournament sets will be Best of 3 until Top 32, at which point they will become Best of 5

Stagelist
For Game 1, the stage will be selected by a 1-2-1 ban order (with the lower seeded player banning first)
For subsequent games: the winner of the previous game may ban THREE stages. The loser may then pick from the remaining stages
Full DSR is in effect, meaning that no player may counterpick to ANY stage on which they've previously won a game during the current set

During Pools:
All tournament sets played in Pools will be played on the workshop version of the stagelist

During Main Bracket:
Competitors have an options between workshop or basecast stages

DQ Timers:
The first round of Winner's side will have a 10 minute automatic disqualification timer, all subsequent rounds (including all of Loser's Bracket) will have a 5 minute timer.
The timer will return to 10 minutes for the first round of Main Bracket as well.
If your opponent does not show up for 10 minutes after checking in, use the "Call Moderator" function on smash.gg and a TO will be along to assess the situation. If they are delaying bracket, they will be disqualified into losers.

Misc:
If alerted by your opponent you MUST changes alts if requested, if requested during the first 5 seconds of the game, the game will be restarted
If alerted by your opponent you MUST turn off voice modes if requested, if requested during the first 5 seconds of the game, the game will be restarted 
All alternative modes on characters WILL NOT be allowed

In the event of a lag test:
A LAN connection IS required for participation in this tournament.
In the event of a lag test, both players must provide proof of LAN or confirm that they are playing on a wireless connection.
Minimum specifications for a "stable connection" are considered to be a "Ping" under 30 ms and an "Upload Speed" above 10 mb/s.
If there is a vast difference between the player's internet speeds, it is up to TO discretion to determine who is the cause of the lag using these guidelines.

Rules-Notes:
AMAKUSA-SPECIFIC: Due to increased desync bugs associated with this character, you MUST set your delay frames to 3 if someone plays this character.

DESYNCS: Samurai Shodown rollback is subject to many desync-related bugs. In the event of a room crash, the default policy is to replay the game regardless of rounds and rage meter.

Games commonly desync for one player at the end of matches. The losing player's game will freeze, but the winning player will "play it out" as if they won. If this happens, the "losing" player should show a screenshot of the freeze to a TO so that we know to have the match replayed.

Players are entitled to either of the following:
1) A lag test game before their set starts
2) A host-swap request to help mitigate netcode problems
Please let a TO know if you'd like either of these.

STAGES: Due to the presence/absence of foreground objects that may contribute to rollback issues, please follow these guidelines for stages:
Recommended: Nikko, Kabuki Estate, Dojo, Greenhell
Recommended against: Mikatagahara Field, Sumida River, Galleon

Players have the right to insist on a recommended stage.

DELAY FRAME GUIDELINES: Try to use 1 delay frame for every 50ms of ping. E.g. 1 frame for 57ms, 2 frames for 104ms, etc.
$-Prizes: Prizes from SNK potentially if we can reach out to them

Rules-Glitches:
If the disc overpasses the goal, it can very rarely cause scoring to happen over and over. If this bug happens, please let a TO know to allow the game to be restored to the most logical point before the glitch.

Any other disputes please message a TO.

Rules-Notes:
In-game settings: Set Time 90, Set Points 15, Winning Sets 2.

Random Start: First stage per match is set to Random. Hit the random button twice, then hit select to lock in the stage.

Banned stage: Casino. If selected on accident, exit the match and select another stage. 

Winner is character locked, loser may counter-pick both stage and character.

Matches are 2/3 (Excepting Winners Grand Finals, 3/5).

If Sudden Death occurs and no players score, return to the same stage, with the same characters. First player to score wins.

Dave's Stupid Rule: a Player may not choose a stage on which they have previously won within the current match.
